          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              <div class="quotetitle">LordHunter317 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">ShuggyCoUk wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Likewise, data corruption and loss is a real thing that happens</div><br /><br />MD5 hashes for *everything*. At least you know it has happened...</div>That's great if the data is corrupted once you store it.  It doesn't help you if the sensor goes out to lunch, or if there are other problems prior to/at acquisition.</div><br /><br />That's what the internal consistency checking does. <br />Validate it forms a self consistent result for the entire day. <br /><br />This validation involves running the system that will eventually consume it against it enabling several very aggressive sanity checks over and above what it would normally do. This isn't just counting things. <br /><br />Like I said, we catch bugs in the *exchange* doing this.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
