        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Clearly I should have explained myself better initially.   Data corruption is a real physical thing, that will happen with your raw data no matter what.  Physics, unfortunately, demands it.<br /><br />Yes, in some processes, you can do checking after the fact to detect and/or correct some errors, possibly all errors.  However, this is not always the case.  <br /><br />Despite all of that, it doesn't change that you should treat the raw data as the most important thing, even though it may be (will be) imperfect and incorret.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
