              Is it me or is Python quirky? To me, it's much better if months are 0-based; modular arithmetic is easier and jives better with 0-based arrays... Why would they be 1-based? I know display of months is 1-based, but it's better to handle that in the display layer instead of having that permeate the internals and make them more complex. <br /><br />I know Java months are 0-based... so are everyone else's, right?

              

              
              
