              I thought the point of the datetime module was so you didn't need to do stuff like modular arithmetic on months. I can see the argument for 0 based (and presumably the same with days?), but there's a clear trade-off between that and having an intuitive interface.<br /><br />It is a bit weird that timedelta doesn't support dates (or that there's no datadelta equivalent), so I guess it can't do what you want. I did just find <a href="http://labix.org/python-dateutil" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">dateutil</a> which allows such things but that's a 3rd-party dependency.

              

              
              
